\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line CAT is a private college not yet registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training\'3B and it is not yet accredited to offer higher education programmes. \line \line The Accreditation Committee decided at its meeting of 23 and 24 February 2011 to defer this programme pending the submission of additional information. The communication was sent to the institution requesting clarity on the following \'3A\line \line 1. The institution must describe in detail the outcome of the programme\'3B provide a purpose statement for each module and rules of combination.\line 2. The institution needs to submit an updated admissions policy that adheres to current legislation.\line  The institution needs to submit a policy document indicating clearly how the institution intends\line  to ensure the integrity of the certification processes for the qualification.\line 3. The institution must provide a plan indicating how it will ensure that suitable and sufficient\line  library resources exist which complement the curriculum and that policies exist for the proper\line  management and maintenance of library resources.\line 4. The institution must provide an updated policy and procedures indicating clearly how the\line  institution intends to ensure that all assessment for exit level modules is externally moderated\line  and that external moderators are appropriately chosen in terms of guidelines developed by the\line  institution.\line 5. The institution needs to submit an appropriate policy and procedures for RPL.\line \cell \pard 

