\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator has perused the additional information supplied with the original submission and found that all minimum standards are complied with. \line \line The programme is of three-year duration and has a total credit value of 375. A total of 45 credits is pitched at NQF Level 5\'2C 270 credits at NQF Level 6 and 60 credits at NQF Level 7. These meet the requirements of the HEQF for a Diploma at NQF Level 6. However\'2C the new HEQF does not make provision for a national diploma. The programme should be renamed a Diploma in Computer Applications at NQF Level 6 so that it is correctly aligned to the HEQF \'28Crt 1 \'28ii\'29\'29. \line \line The structure of the programme has a mix of compulsory and elective modules which allows learners appropriate choices in career pathways in the IT field. The teaching and learning methods includes face-to-face\'2C practical work on the computer\'2C projects and experiential learning in the workplace\'2C all of which are credit bearing. Learning material\'2C which is provided to students\'2C and the prescribed text\'2C allow learners to engage in self-study. Tutorials conducted to small groups are also a positive feature. The outcomes of the programme and of each module are made explicit.  The institution has specified the exit levels outcomes as well the competencies relevant to the NQF level of the programme \'28Criterion 1 \'28iii\'29\'29. The programme design has a good balance between theoretical\'2C practical and experiential knowledge and skills. The scope of each module will give students sufficient depth in knowledge and skills to enable learners gain mastery of each discipline or field of study.\line \line The admission and selection requirements are appropriate to the programme and to the target group. The institution has ensured that the requirements of Umalusi are met for general admission. \line \line All academic staff members identified for the programme have appropriate postgraduate qualifications. All full-time academic staff members have sufficient teaching experience.\line \line In terms of teaching and learning the operating documents clearly illustrate that a teaching and learning strategy is in place that is relevant to the needs of students. A good mix of appropriate teaching methods will be employed by staff members who are trained in its implementation.  Feedback mechanisms have been identified. Processes are in place for internal moderation. A clear policy exits for external moderation.  The institution\'E2\'80\'99s recording of assessment results is secure and reliable. A document exists that specifies the process for settling students\'E2\'80\'99 disputes and for an appeals process.\line \line The IT infrastructure for the delivery of the programme is sufficient and suitable both in terms of hardware and software and web access. Suitable arrangements are in place for the maintenance and upgrade of the facilities. A budget is in place for the purchase of new computers and students may borrow computers to take home.  The institution has a well-equipped library with internet access. Appropriate on-line facilities exist for research. \line \line The Directorate concurs with the recommendation that the programme should be accredited.\line \cell \pard 

